properties.Name: Atm
properties.Description:
A unmanned terminal that carries out automated teller functions such as
- dispensing cash
- account enquiries
- check deposit acceptance

The two most common ATMs are Through-the-Wall (Wall Mounted) ATMs and Stand-Alone (Convenience) cash machines.

Columns.Name: AtmId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an ATM.

Columns.Name: AtmSerialNumber
Columns.Description: The serial number of the ATM machine.

Columns.Name: InstallationDate
Columns.Description: The date that the ATM was installed.

Columns.Name: AtmServiceTelephoneNumber
Columns.Description: The telephone number to call for service on the ATM machine.

Columns.Name: AtmConfigurationTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an ATM Configuration Type.

Columns.Name: IssuerId
Columns.Description:
The unique identifier of an Issuer.

The first 6 digits of the credit card number are known as the Issuer Identification Number (IIN). These identify the institution that issued the card to the card holder.

Columns.Name: MerchantId
Columns.Description:
The Merchant Identification (MID) is a unique number that identifies your merchant account to payment processing networks and to your payment software.

A series or group of digits that uniquely identifies the merchant to the merchant signing bank for account and billing purposes. 

When a merchant retains the services of a credit card processor, it is issued a merchant ID.

Columns.Name: ChannelId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Channel.

Columns.Name: FinancialInstitutionId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Financial Institution.
